                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Agile",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 282",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 282",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 282,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "The multiple attack penalty you take with this weapon on the second attack on your turn is \u20134 instead of \u20135, and \u20138 instead of \u201310 on the third and subsequent attacks in the turn.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "remastered",
                  "aonid": 602,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "9205dbb5fc7a16fe38ebed77c30d1a29",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Finesse",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 282",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 282",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 282,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "You can use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls using this melee weapon. You still use your Strength modifier when calculating damage.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "remastered",
                  "aonid": 661,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "8b39d7aef2d11946dd28e3dfc7a7ff91",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Nonlethal",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 283",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 283",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 283,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "An effect with this trait is not inherently deadly. Damage from a nonlethal effect knocks a creature out rather than killing it. You can use a nonlethal weapon to make a lethal attack with a \u20132 circumstance penalty.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "remastered",
                  "aonid": 719,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "f95dccf28216f1330ef2dd9decad87fb",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "alt": "Disarmed",
                    "aonid": 41,
                    "game-obj": "Actions",
                    "name": "Disarmed",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  {
                    "alt": "free-hand",
                    "aonid": 181,
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "name": "free-hand",
                    "type": "link"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "Unarmed",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 283",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 283",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 283,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "An unarmed attack uses your body rather than a manufactured weapon. An unarmed attack isn't a weapon, though it's categorized with weapons for weapon groups, and it might have weapon traits. Since it's part of your body, an unarmed attack can't be Disarmed. It also doesn't take up a hand, though a fist or other grasping appendage generally works like a free-hand weapon.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
