                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 629,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "An alchemical bomb combines volatile alchemical components that explode when the bomb hits a creature or object. Most alchemical bombs deal damage, though some produce other effects.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "104d6fc2d1d7f97108e1e9b4be5089b1",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "links": [
                  {
                    "alt": "range increments",
                    "aonid": 227,
                    "game-obj": "Rules",
                    "name": "range increments",
                    "type": "link"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "Range",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Bestiary pg. 17",
                      "aonid": 2,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Bestiary pg. 17",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Bestiary",
                    "page": 17,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "These attacks will either list a finite range or a range increment, which follows the normal rules for range increments.",
                "type": "trait",
                "value": "increment 20 feet"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "remastered",
                  "aonid": 699,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "legacy",
                "game-id": "a0d3f3d449a02a84abc3edb47ba69b02",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Splash",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "4.0",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "4.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                      "aonid": 1,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Core Rulebook",
                    "page": 637,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "When you use a thrown weapon with the splash trait, you don\u2019t add your Strength modifier to the damage roll. If an attack with a splash weapon fails, succeeds, or critically succeeds, all creatures within 5 feet of the target (including the target) take the listed splash damage. On a failure (but not a critical failure), the target of the attack still takes the splash damage. Add splash damage together with the initial damage against the target before applying the target\u2019s weaknesses or resistances. You don\u2019t multiply splash damage on a critical hit.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
